trashday.model

Class IntentLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • trashday.model.IntentLog

  • public class IntentLog
extends Object
    Data structure for storing user activity log.

    The log keeps a weekly total of the type and number of user interactions Trash Day sees per-user. Application stores up to 12 weeks of data to help analyze user usage patterns.

    The class implements Jackson Model Versioning using the "@JsonVersionedModel" and ToCurrentIntentLog class.

    Author:
    J. Todd Baldwin
    See Also:
    Jackson Module: Model Versioning

    • Method Detail

      • incrementIntent

        public void incrementIntent(String yearWeek,
                            String intentName,
                            Integer count)
        Increment the IntentLog count for the given intentName that occurred in the given yearWeek (eg. 2014-38). IntentLog stores counts each intentName occurred on a per-week basis.
        Parameters:
        yearWeek - String in form YYYY-ww when the intentName occurred
        intentName - String of the intent invoked by the user of the application.
        count - Integer of how many times this intentName occurred within the week corresponding to the ldtEntry

      • prune

        public void prune(int weeksEntriesToKeep)
        Prune to a maximum number of weeks of log data kept. Currently keep up to 12 weeks of user interaction log. Called before saving IntentLog objects to Dynamo DB.
        Parameters:
        weeksEntriesToKeep - int Number of weeks to keep in this IntentLog.
